Really????  What about the other 2 files i posted?  You can&#39;t deny 
that there is some sort of communication going on, even the hardest 
skeptics as yourself have to admit the validity of those files.  I 
believe in a random chance of a stray radio signal coinsiding with 
the question asked at that time, but after 2 years and 4000 files 
later i have to believe that this communication is real.  I also use 
other methods that do not involve a radio at all, what could make 
that happen?  These are all good questions to make someone re-think 
their stance on RTSC and other ITC devices.  How can a scrambled up 
file on a computer program called evpmaker say full sentences up to 
25 words in length?  Did i mention that the original file that was 
used had no words in it at all, only bits and pieces of audio 
segments.  Something to think about anyway.  I used to stand on your 
side of the fence, but after a while it can no longer be ignored that 
what we are hearing is really happening.

-Steve H.



